                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13607881" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 17:23:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you be more precises what is the problem?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Line 60 is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                            populateStatement(ps, i, expected);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It has nothing to do if body is null etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13607883" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 17:24:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The sql component does not look for parameters in headers, only the body.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13608131" author="jonasf" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 20:19:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I find line 60 to be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt; 
                if (exchange.getIn().getBody() != null) {
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As seen in the repository here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/camel/trunk/components/camel-sql/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/sql/SqlProducer.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/camel/trunk/components/camel-sql/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/sql/SqlProducer.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I believe the documentation clearly states that the headers are searched for parameters and the code does actually do this. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;When using named parameters, Camel will lookup the names from, in the given precedence:&lt;br/&gt;
1. from message body if its a java.util.Map&lt;br/&gt;
2. from message headers&quot; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/sql-component.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/sql-component.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;By just removing the if statement the code works. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13608777" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 21 Mar 2013 09:10:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah I was looking at the camel-sql component for 2.10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yeah I am fixing this now on 2.11.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13608778" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 21 Mar 2013 09:17:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug only applies to 2.11&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
